Spring Rest:

@RestController - Applied over the Rest Controller Class to Create a Bean during the Startup
@RequestMapping - Handle Any HTTP Request (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, etc)
                - attributes - path -> endpoint of the RestController
                             - produces -> Specifies the Media Type of Handler method produces.
                             - consumes
                             - method
                             - headers  - The handler method will be invoked only if the header of specific type is pased in the request.
                                        - headers = "content-type=application/json"
                                            
